The paper discusses the use of logic programming, specifically answer set programming (ASP), to solve search problems beyond NP. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of disjunctive logic programs, which is a subfield of programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The development of a proof-of-concept implementation involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
